<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<title>W3.CSS</title>
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://www.w3schools.com/w3css/4/w3.css">
<body>

<div class="w3-sidebar w3-bar-block w3-card-2 w3-animate-left" style="display:none" id="mySidebar">
  <button class="w3-bar-item w3-button w3-large"
  onclick="w3_close()">Close</button>
  <a href="#" class="w3-bar-item w3-button">Restaurants</a>
  <a href="#" class="w3-bar-item w3-button">Points of Interest</a>
  <a href="#" class="w3-bar-item w3-button">.</a>
  <a href="#" class="w3-bar-item w3-button">.</a>
  <a href="#" class="w3-bar-item w3-button">.</a>
  <a href="#" class="w3-bar-item w3-button">Interactive Map</a>
</div>

<div id="main">

<div class="w3-teal">
  <button id="openNav" class="w3-button w3-teal w3-xlarge" onclick="w3_open()">&#9776;</button>
  <div class="w3-container" style="display:inline-block;">
    <h1 style="text-align:center;">Welcome to Chinatown!</h1>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- <img src="img_car.jpg" alt="Car" style="width:100%"> -->

<div class="w3-container">
<p>In this example, the sidebar is hidden (style="display:none")</p>
<p>It is shown when you click on the menu icon in the top left corner.</p>
<p>When it is opened, it shifts the page content to the right.</p>
<p>We use JavaScript to add a 25% left margin to the div element with id="main" when this happens. The value "25%" matches the width of the sidebar.</p>
</div>

</div>

<script>
function w3_open() {
  document.getElementById("main").style.marginLeft = "25%";
  document.getElementById("mySidebar").style.width = "25%";
  document.getElementById("mySidebar").style.display = "block";
  document.getElementById("openNav").style.display = 'none';
}
function w3_close() {
  document.getElementById("main").style.marginLeft = "0%";
  document.getElementById("mySidebar").style.display = "none";
  document.getElementById("openNav").style.display = "inline-block";
}
</script>

</body>
</html>

